ies in Highly Sensitive Contexts -- t‘The Emotional Work is Part of the Work’: Strategies to Maintain Researcher Emotional and Psychological Safety During Challenging Fieldwork -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aBringing together a team of international scholars, this volume provides a foundational guide to queer methodologies in the study of political violence and conflict. Contributors provide illuminating discussions on why queer approaches are important, what they entail and how to utilise a queer approach to political violence and conflict. The chapters explore a variety of methodological approaches, including fieldwork, interviews, cultural analysis and archival research. They also engage with broader academic debates, such as how to work with research partners in an ethical manner. Including valuable case studies from around the world, the book demonstrates how these methods can be used in practice. It is the first critical, in-depth discussion on queer methods and methodologies for research on political violence and conflict.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aConflict (Psychology). 0aPolitical violence. 0aQueer theory. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Geopolitics.2bisacsh1 aBerchtold, Helena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCabrera, Cristian González, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper-Cunningham, Dean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelatolla, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelatolla, Andrew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aErdem, Zeynep Pınar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreed, Maureen, econtributor.4ctb